<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the United
                                    States</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President of
                                    Chile</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Mansion</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>On behalf of the sufferers at Galveston, and in the name of the sorrowing
                            people of this country, I gratefully acknowledge your excellency’s
                            message of condolence.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                            McKinley.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>